title.narrative: 3.2 Boys, girls and women at risk or survivors of violence have access to an integrated package of quality prevention and responseservices in most disadvantaged localities in Lebanon

description.narrative: Due to the worsening economic and social crisis in the country, protection needs for children and women escalated tremendously during the year. UNICEF and partners met the expected target beneficiaries accessing services for protection risk mitigation and response. More than 79,655 children and women at risk or survivors of violence, abuse and exploitation were reached by professional services and support, including through case management, focused non-specialized psycho-social support, safe spaces for women and girls at risk of gender-based violence, while building long-term capacity of service providers. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/12/2021
